items.title: Runtime v9340 Upgrade On Kusama: Fixing OpenGov Parameters and more!
items.content: The proposal aims to upgrade Kusama's runtime to [v9340](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/releases/tag/v0.9.34): more information about Gov2 can be found in the release notes.  **Runtime**  \[S\] ✅ audited [#12310](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12310) Low - Asset pallet: support repeated destroys to safely destroy large assets  \[S\] ⏳ pending non-critical audit [#12730](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12730) Low - Allow alliance fellows to give up voting rights  \[P\] ✅ trivial [#6326](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/pull/6326) Low - Add collectives as trusted teleporter  \[P\] ✅ trivial [#6366](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/pull/6366) Low - OpenGov: Proxy definitions  \[S\] ✅ trivial [#12808](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12808) Low - Bounties use SpendOrigin  \[S\] ✅ trivial [#12610](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12610) Low - Non-interactive staking  \[S\] ✅ trivial [#12842](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12842) Low - OpenGov: abstentions  \[P\] ✅ trivial [#6390](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/pull/6390) Low - Allow Root with OpenGov origins  \[S\] [#12848](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/12848) Low - Add `with_weight` extrinsic  \[P\] ✅ trivial [#6372](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/pull/6372) Low - OpenGov: Kusama tweaks   Proposal hash: `0x0debc0e862468363f53cf1ea4d451ec2fdfc4aeb37a3189354df9597636c55b9`  Note this proposal is submitted with `set_storage` call, not `set_code` call (more info on why `set_code` won't work can be found on [this post](https://polkadot.polkassembly.io/motion/306)).  Preimage:  ![](https://i.ibb.co/bbKw1tx/Screenshot-2022-12-07-at-09-53-08.png)  You can review the hash and changes in the release notes and use `SRTool` to verify the proposal hash - make sure to vote at your convenience! This proposal is submitted as an **external motion**: meaning after the Council vote, the community will need to vote on the proposal in the referenda queue.

items.title: Fixing the Last Auctions From The Auctions Schedule - Kusama Network
items.content: With OpenGov up and running on Kusama, the current auctions [schedule](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/motion/438) suffers an enactment issue: all pending auctions won’t enact successfully, although scheduled, due to a `BadOrigin` error: [https://kusama.subscan.io/block/15523200?tab=event&&event=15523200-16](https://kusama.subscan.io/block/15523200?tab=event&&event=15523200-16). This is because with OpenGov, an auction needs the [`AuctionAdmin` origin](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/blob/v0.9.32/runtime/kusama/src/lib.rs#L1245) to be enacted successfully, but the original auctions for LP25 had the origin of more than 3/5 Council. ```  [    [      15,724,800    ]    [      {        maybeId: 0xf31cf33afabfc39818c20e858c4ceded9bf70cb3d29d460adc468af33853873c        priority: 0        call: {          Inline: 0x4800e2a5010068        }        maybePeriodic: [          100,800          2        ]        origin: {          Council: {            Members: [              13              19            ]          }        }      }    ]  ]```With this new proposal we aim to include the last auctions on LP26 + the ones what were not enacted on LP25, now to be included on LP27. A new calendar for auctions will be proposed soon in OpenGov, but since this one is a legacy proposal, approved by the community and not working due to a problem with origins, It would be ideal to fast-track to enact ASAP. - Proposal Hash: `0x3f303aa09336575dd393dd38f26b1db6fe46eb8fb082b6abae93aa2bf79cd0e3`- Primate submission: [https://kusama.subscan.io/extrinsic/15580971-7](https://kusama.subscan.io/extrinsic/15580971-7) - Image can be found [here](https://polkadot.js.org/apps/?rpc=wss%3A%2F%2Fkusama-rpc.polkadot.io#/extrinsics/decode/0x1804081d052bd1e9469fc73e572f6019b15ab507656fa8b34937ee212544eb877c5c6dd0da0000000001c089010004000000004800e2a50100681d05337955059e29e88811a9ffbbcdc33a57bb70ce142b89f935fbeb795507e3f2482043060001c089010002000000004800e2a501006c)

items.title: Fixing the disappeared approved proposals (by the community) on relaychain from Genshiro and Kintsugi
items.content:
This proposal (hopefully the last one for Council) is now up for vote on Kusama:

With the [v9320 runtime upgrade](https://kusama.subsquare.io/democracy/referendum/244), an issue with migration appeared: the migration did not work for preimages submitted before the upgrade as well as for proposals approved by the community and on dispatch queue. This included: 
- [Genshiro's proposal](https://kusama.subsquare.io/democracy/referendum/246) to swap slots, already approved by the community and on dispatch queue.
- [Kintsugi’s proposal](https://kusama.polkassembly.io/referendum/242) to open an HRMP channel with Statemine, already approved by the community and on dispatch queue.

In order to make sure the approval by the community is held as true, we aim to vote again on these two proposals to have then enacted as decided by the community, in time. For this, the proposal is composed by a `batch` call including: a `forceOpenHrmpChannel` (for Kintsugi and Statemine) with a `forceTransfer` call from treasury to pay for the cost of the channel opening, and a `registrarSwap` call (for Genshiro). We aim to vote this ASAP to pass it to vote. Preimage is submitted. 

- Call hash: `0x83c439b8b621a3507c90c8a3ebd0c4b3d76962f853e1f11858e665aeafaeac14`
- Call data: `0x1804140402006d6f646c70792f747273727900000000000000000000000000000000000000000070617261e80300000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000b00a0724e18093c07e80300002c080000e8030000009001003c072c080000e8030000e8030000009001004603b2080000e80700004603e8070000b2080000`
- Composition can be found [HERE](https://i.ibb.co/b6VZ48J/Screenshot-2022-11-23-at-15-29-48.png) and [HERE](https://i.ibb.co/pn03Ssm/Screenshot-2022-11-23-at-15-29-56.png).

Please vote at your convenience! This is submitted as an external motion: after Council approval the community will vote on this.

All council members please vote at your earliest convenience!

items.title: Upgrade of Kusama Runtime to v2026
items.content:
**Motion 234 upgrading Kusama Runtime to v2026 is up for vote**

Update priority: **Medium** (timely upgrade recommended) due to changes: Fixes logging of target names with dashes ([#7281](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/7281)), No longer actively open legacy substreams ([#7076](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/7076)), Make queryStorage and storagePairs unsafe RPC functions ([#7342](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/pull/7342)).

Release notes and hash can be found [here](https://github.com/paritytech/polkadot/releases/tag/v0.8.26). All council members please vote at your earliest convenience.
